  "text": "For completeness we like to refer to Table 3 in Appendix B, where we list fitted parameters, p values and the result of log-likelihood tests, conducted using the method of Virkar and Clauset [CITATION_1] . As shown in the table, the larger the used binsizes, the higher the p values indicating that a power-law fits the data. For small binsizes (low p values) the results are not conclusive or rather in favor of a lognormal distribution.",
